    {
      "id": "853e92aa33831558f49d3bb841d146da821f23c0",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 12,
        "name": "wangdi",
        "email": "di.wang@intel.com",
        "username": "wangdi",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-02-13 03:41:24.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nHmm, probably my commit message is confused, or I miss sth here. But I thought we will keep using ostid during mds and ost communication, i.e. always do fid_ostid_pack during pack RPC on the MDS, and do fid_ostid_unpack on the OST upon receiving RPC, even after fid on OST is enabled. \n\nAs for this bug, it is the MDS accidentally using the wrong packing method ostid_fid_pack (should be fid_ostid_pack actually), which does not convert the IDIF fid properly to ostid, then it cause the panic on the OST side.\n\nI will update the comment here.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
